Commentary Text: Nathan Ellis to Aman Hakim Khan, out Caught by Harpreet Brar!! Harpreet Brar can do no wrong today. It was a 127ks short ball outside off, didn't really have any venom on it but lack of pace seem to have messed up the timing. Aman Hakim Khan pulled firmly but the lack of timing was very evident from the onset. Went flat to the right of deep mid-wicket and Harpreet collects an excellent low catch running forward. He might have miscalculated the timing of the dip but never looked hurried running towards the ball. Is this the game for PBKS? Aman Hakim Khan c Harpreet Brar b Nathan Ellis 16(18) [4s-1 6s-1]

Commentary Text: Harpreet Brar to Warner, out Lbw!! Gee, this didn't look close. Perhaps the appeal from the bowler wasn't strong either. Warner was casually chatting and smiling with Axar, but he's caught dead in front of the stumps. Hitting the top of leg-stump. It was tossed up, pitched on middle and drifted in ever so slightly to beat Warner on the inside edge. PBKS went up for the review in some hope and they found great joy in return.... Warner lbw b Harpreet Brar 54(27) [4s-10 6s-1]

Commentary Text: Harpreet Brar to Philip Salt, out Bowled!! Harpreet Brar outfoxes Philip Salt and this is a big breakthrough for PBKS! Smart piece of bowling from the left-arm orthodox. He bowls this one a bit quicker and this one doesn't turn away. This one keeps on coming in with the arm. This is where Philip Salt is beaten for pace and the ball goes past his attempted cut to shatter the stumps. Philip Salt b Harpreet Brar 21(17) [4s-3]
